1) Display third column of filename.csv without printing the header "CGPA" also sort the same
A) cut -d , -f 3 shadow.csv | grep -v CGPA | sort -g

2) Display only current time using date command
A) date +'%r'

3) Use Unique with all possible options
A) uniq -u shadowuni.csv
   uniq -D shadowuni.csv
   uniq -d shadowuni.csv

4) Print number of lines for ls -l command
A) 

5) Display USN from 7-14 along with other fields
A) head -n 15 shadowusn.csv | tail -n 8

6) Write a shell script to print only date and time from date command?
A) echo The date and time is $(date +%D..%r)

7) Write a shell script to check whether a number is +ve or -ve?
A) echo "Enter a Number:"
   read n
   if [ $n -gt 0 ]
   then
	   echo "Number is positive"
   else if [ $n -eq 0 ]
   then
	   echo "Number is Zero"
   else 
	   echo "Number is negative"
   fi
   fi



